         <Description>The linewidth observable refers to the FWHM of the (assumed) Gaussian absorption line profile for the 6173.3 Å line on the surface of the sun.

HMI samples the Fe I absorption line at 6173.3 Å at six points. Assuming that the &quot;pure&quot; solar Fe I line profile is a Gaussian, and the HMI filter filter transmission profiles are delta functions, the first and second Fourier coefficients of the of the Fe I line can be calculated and an estimate of the Doppler Velocity can be made. An estimate (proxy) for the continuum intensity Ic is obtained by &quot;reconstructing&quot; the solar line from the estimates of the Doppler shift λo, the linewidth σ, and the linedepth Id. More details can be found at http://jsoc.stanford.edu/relevant_papers/observables.pdf.</Description>
